---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Professional Reflection" activeTab="uni">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto relative z-10">
    
    <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-4 text-industrial-black">Professional Reflection</h1>
        <p class="text-order-3 text-brand-purple tracking-[0.4em] font-bold">Internship Evaluation & Career Trajectory</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-32 pb-48">
        
        <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
            {/* LEFT COLUMN: EXPECTATIONS */}
            <div class="space-y-8">
                <h2 class="text-order-1 text-brand-purple text-left">01 // Expectations</h2>
                <div class="text-order-2 text-left space-y-4">
                    <p>
                        I didn’t have many expectations as I tried to keep an open mind as to what to expect. 
                        I suppose I expected the work to include elements of hands-on experience, the other 
                        workers to be friendly, and that this would be a great opportunity to expand my 
                        knowledge to further my career.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            {/* RIGHT COLUMN: REALITY */}
            <div class="space-y-8">
                <h2 class="text-order-1 text-brand-purple text-right">Reality \\ 02</h2>
                <div class="text-order-2 text-right space-y-4">
                    <p>
                        It didn’t differ much from my expectations. I suppose there has been a bit more 
                        paperwork than what I was initially expecting although a certain amount of 
                        paperwork was anticipated.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        The people have been friendlier than I could have thought, and the working 
                        environment more welcoming and less daunting.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white/50 p-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
            <h2 class="text-order-1 text-brand-orange mb-12">03 // Core Industrial Lessons</h2>
            <div class="space-y-8">
                <p class="text-order-2">
                    The most important lessons from my internship have been to be **open to change, be adaptable, and be talkative.** The ability to be open to change and being adaptable go hand in hand, as when things start to go sideways or don’t go perfectly to plan you have to be able to manage it effectively no matter how off track the task or project goes.
                </p>
                <p class="text-order-2">
                    Being talkative is always important, more accurately the ability to communicate, as without communication often misunderstandings can arise and lead to further confusion and increase the risk of derailment of projects. Further to this being talkative and being able to communicate has led to better relationships within teams and has further made the working environment that much more comfortable, both for working and for being able to reach out when issues have arisen.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-order-1 text-industrial-black mb-12">04 // Value Proposition</h2>
            <div class="space-y-12">
                <p class="text-2xl font-black uppercase text-industrial-black leading-tight border-l-4 border-brand-orange pl-8">
                    "I am a mechatronic engineer driven by the physical build. I specialize in high-precision mechanical design and technical execution, transforming designs into functional assets through <span class="text-brand-orange">direct production involvement</span>, and closing the loop with comprehensive documentation and dedicated lifecycle support."
                </p>
                
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-12">
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <h4 class="text-order-1 text-brand-orange">Process Improvement & Adaptability</h4>
                        <p class="text-order-2">I successfully transitioned to and learned the new job/stock/quoting management system and proactively noted down areas for improvement to operations. A key example is reformatting the customer visitation record from a working document to a traceability table in Excel to allow for better tracking and follow-up.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <h4 class="text-order-1 text-brand-orange">Systems Implementation & Analysis</h4>
                        <p class="text-order-2">I participated in and helped to lead internal discussions regarding the potential rollout of Autodesk Vault Pro into the company's workflow, demonstrating an interest and capability in enterprise system adoption.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <h4 class="text-order-1 text-brand-orange">Technical Communication</h4>
                        <p class="text-order-2">I was tasked with and successfully completed multiple technical writing projects, including writing up comprehensive user manuals for the Schenck Balancing rotor and the centrifuge stripping process. This work was essential for sharing institutional knowledge, training new staff, and ensuring operational consistency.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-order-1 text-brand-purple mb-12">05 // Career Influence & Trajectory</h2>
            <div class="space-y-12">
                <p class="text-order-2">
                    The internship has refined my career focus by confirming my foundational interest in hands-on mechanical design and technical execution while also revealing a significant strength in engineering process management and technical communication. 
                </p>
                
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 pt-12 border-t border-slate-200">
                    <div class="space-y-6">
                        <h4 class="text-order-1 text-industrial-black">Design & Hands-on Work</h4>
                        <ul class="space-y-4 text-order-3 text-slate-500">
                            <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">+</span> CAD modeling and drawing of the 1038 Press Shaft Bullnose Intermediate Shaft.</li>
                            <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">+</span> Workshop floor exposure: Schenck Balancing rotor setup and tallow centrifuge stripping.</li>
                            <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">+</span> Testing of gearboxes and bearings.</li>
                            <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">+</span> Project oversight: 1800 Cooker Wear Sleeves repair and Mazak IntegraX 5-axis CNC setup.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="space-y-6">
                        <h4 class="text-order-1 text-industrial-black">Process & Documentation</h4>
                        <ul class="space-y-4 text-order-3 text-slate-500">
                            <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">+</span> Essential user manuals for the balancing machine and centrifuge stripping process.</li>
                            <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">+</span> Reformatting customer visit data into traceability tables.</li>
                            <li class="flex gap-4"><span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">+</span> Developed templates for evaluation reports for customers.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>